The original regex `/:.+/` requires at least one character after the colon (`:` followed by one or more characters).
The mutated regex `/:./ ` requires exactly one character after the colon (`:` followed by exactly one character).

So a capture like `:a` (single character name) would match both regexes, but a capture like `:ab` (multi-character name) would only match the original.

